Music star Teni Makanaki has given $1,000 to a toddler in Lagos. The ‘Uyo Meyo’ singer made the donation during a business conference last Saturday where she performed to guests at the conference. Grace Oriaghan, a beauty expert and mother of the toddler, whose name was given as Arielle, made the announcement on Twitter on Sunday.   YCee scolds Man Utd star Greenwood over alleged rape     Wizkid speaks on new album     Popular skitmaker Isbae U faces alleged sex-for-skits…   “My baby became a #RiseBaby yesterday after TeniEntertainer gifted her $1,000 - Advertisement - “At the Risevest conference. I still can’t believe that happened,” she confirmed. Confirming the development, owners of Rise responded to the tweet. “The beautiful moment when baby Arielle got a $1,000 Rise plan as a gift from the legendary TeniEntertainer! She’s on her way to a secure financial future.”